    {
      "recipeDescriptionLine": "Dal Tadka is a thick stew prepared with different varieties. It is generally pressure cooked with very basic ingredients and seasoned to enhance flavor. It is widely eaten along with rice and rotis."
    },
    {
      "recipeDescriptionLine": "Dal is god source of dietary fiber, protein and low in sodium and cholestrol. Studies have also shown that consuming pulses can result in more stable blood glucose levels after meals due to its lower glycemic index."
    },
    {
      "recipeDescriptionLine": "Dal tadka is basically prepare with Toor dal also known as Arhar, Tuvar and Split Pigeon Peas."
    }
